{# 
    Strikethrough Text (<strike>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines text that is no longer correct or relevant, typically displayed
    with a strikethrough.

    Variables:
    - `strike_text`: The text to be displayed with a strikethrough. Defaults to "Strikethrough text".

    Notes:
    - The <strike> element is deprecated in HTML5 and should not be used. Consider using the <s> element or CSS text-decoration property instead.
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/strike
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_strike.asp

#}

<strike>{{ strike_text | default('Strikethrough text') | e }}</strike>
